title: Defenders recognized for helping rescue woman attacked by yellow jackets [Image 3 of 3]
text:
Col. Lauren Courchaine, 37th Training Wing commander, and Chief Master Sgt. Michael Morgan, 37th TRW Command Chief, flank Security Forces instructors (from left to right): Staff Sgt. Trevis Merrit, Staff Sgt. Kimberly Carrillo, Tech. Sgt. Shanae Zimmerman, and Staff Sgt. Markale Lovelace, all members of the 343rd Training Squadron, Joint Base San Antonio-Lackland, Texas, May 24, 2023. The leaders visited the lab to publicly recognize the instructors who helped rescue a woman being attacked by yellow jackets. First responders credited the Airmen for saving the womanâ€™s life. (U.S. Air Force photo by Vanessa R. Adame)
